Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Gayle, out Bowled!! Oh what a yorker and he's got him for 99. Gayle is absolutely pissed. Loses his cool and swings the bat in disappointment, loses grip and it flies towards short mid-wicket. Archer congratulates him for the knock. Actually not quite a yorker, full and angling in, Gayle missed the flick, off the pad and into the off stump. That's why he was so livid. What a great hand from the Universe Boss. Gayle b Jofra Archer 99(63) [4s-6 6s-8]

Commentary Text: Stokes to Rahul, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! He's done it, Ben Stokes. What a cricketer. What a massive wicket. Timing has not been easy against the oldish ball today. We've seen so many mishits and sometimes edges ran away to the boundary. Rahul wanted to slog this length delivery out of the ground, but lack of pace on the ball and from the pitch meant he lost shape trying hard and deep mid-wicket too a pressure-yet easy catch. End of a fine 120-run partnership. Rahul c Rahul Tewatia b Stokes 46(41) [4s-3 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Mandeep, out Caught by Stokes!! Oh boy! You gotta feel for Mandeep. This is a sizzler from Archer. Too good a delivery to face your first ball. Bounce, pace and on target at the body - almost near the chest/arm-pit. Mandeep jumps in hope to negotiate it, gets too big and in a tangle. Took his eyes off the ball, it strikes the shoulder of the bat and spoons towards point. Stokes bolts forward, dives full-length and grabs it inches above the turf. Such a sharp catch and Mandeep falls for a first-baller. RR and Archer are cock-a-hoop! Just brilliant! Mandeep c Stokes b Jofra Archer 0(1)
